Enable human-friendly date expressions in --from and --to flags. Parse expressions like 'last week', '3 months ago', 'January 2023', 'Q4 2022'. Drastically improves usability for temporal queries without requiring exact ISO timestamps.

## Background & Motivation

Current behavior requires ISO format:
```bash
xf search "meeting" --from 2023-01-01 --to 2023-03-31  # Works
xf search "meeting" --from "last month"               # Error\!
```

Users naturally want to say:
- "from last week"
- "since 3 months ago"
- "in January 2023"
- "during Q4 2022"

This is friction that a good CLI should eliminate.

## Expression Types to Support

### Relative Expressions
| Expression | Meaning |
|------------|---------|
| yesterday | Previous day |
| today | Current day |
| last week | Previous 7 days |
| last month | Previous calendar month |
| last year | Previous calendar year |
| 3 days ago | 3 days before now |
| 2 weeks ago | 14 days before now |
| 6 months ago | 6 months before now |
| past week | Same as "last week" |
| this month | Current calendar month |
| this year | Current calendar year |

### Absolute Expressions
| Expression | Meaning |
|------------|---------|
| January 2023 | 2023-01-01 to 2023-01-31 |
| Jan 2023 | Same as above |
| 2023-01 | Same as above |
| March 15, 2023 | Specific date |
| Mar 15 2023 | Same as above |

### Period Expressions
| Expression | Meaning |
|------------|---------|
| Q1 2024 | Jan 1 - Mar 31, 2024 |
| Q2 2024 | Apr 1 - Jun 30, 2024 |
| Q3 2024 | Jul 1 - Sep 30, 2024 |
| Q4 2024 | Oct 1 - Dec 31, 2024 |
| summer 2023 | Jun 1 - Aug 31, 2023 |
| winter 2023 | Dec 1, 2023 - Feb 28, 2024 |
| spring 2023 | Mar 1 - May 31, 2023 |
| fall 2023 | Sep 1 - Nov 30, 2023 |

## Technical Approach

### Option A: Use chrono-english crate
```toml
[dependencies]
chrono-english = "0.1"
```

Pros: Well-tested, handles many cases
Cons: May not support all our expressions

### Option B: Custom parser with nom
Build tailored parser for exactly our needs.

Pros: Full control, optimized for our use case
Cons: More code to maintain

### Recommendation: Hybrid
Use chrono-english for standard cases, add custom parsing for:
- Quarter expressions (Q1, Q2, etc.)
- Season expressions (summer, winter, etc.)
- Shorthand months (Jan, Feb, etc.)

