### Parsing in main.rs

```rust
fn parse_date_arg(input: &str, is_end: bool) -> Result<DateTime<Utc>> {
    // Try natural language first
    if let Ok(dt) = parse_human_date(input, is_end) {
        return Ok(dt);
    }

    // Fall back to ISO format
    if let Ok(date) = NaiveDate::parse_from_str(input, "%Y-%m-%d") {
        let time = if is_end { 
            NaiveTime::from_hms(23, 59, 59) 
        } else { 
            NaiveTime::from_hms(0, 0, 0) 
        };
        return Ok(date.and_time(time).and_utc());
    }

    Err(anyhow\!("Could not parse date: '{}'", input))
}
```

### Verbose Mode Confirmation

```rust
if cli.verbose {
    if let Some(from) = &parsed_from {
        eprintln\!("Parsed --from '{}' as {}", original, from.format("%Y-%m-%d"));
    }
}
```

## Timezone Handling

- All calculations relative to local timezone
- Store in UTC for consistency
- Display in local timezone unless --utc flag

